    <div class="news-item">
        <span class="date">March 28, 2026</span>
        <p>
            <strong>Houston, We have a Guestbook</strong> - And God bless
            iframes.
        </p>
        <p>
            I finally decided to actually paste the damn thing
            <a href="/Guestbook">here</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <s>It's really out of place since I haven't paid the supporter
                cost for custom CSS yet, but I'll get around to it. I still have
                so much to fix and make first.</s>
        </p>
        <p>
            All that being said, I'd like it if you came and signed it.
            <a href="/Guestbook">Click here to do so</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <sup>Yeah, I put the link in twice. That's how much I want you to
                sign it.</sup>
        </p>

        <p>
            <strong>Update:</strong> It turns out that there was additional
            customization avaliable. That looks better now.
        </p>
        <hr/>
        <p>
            <strong>SUPPLEMENTAL</strong> - If you couldn't tell from the very
            glowing and very shiny link in the navigation bar, I have
            discovered that CSS supports animations.
        </p>
        <p>The world will learn to fear me now. Muahahahaha!</p>
        <p>
            <sup>I heavily apoligize to anyone using an older computer/browser.
                I couldn't resist it.</sup>
        </p>
        <sup>
            <p>
                Also, starting soon, I'm going to tuck older posts away on
                another page.
            </p></sup>
    </div>

    <div class="news-item">
        <span class="date">March 25, 2026</span>
        <p><strong>Arch'd</strong> - No, not <i>that</i> kind of Arch...</p>
        <img
                src="https://i.postimg.cc/sfKQ52FH/IMG_0177.jpg"
                alt="Delicate Arch @@ Arches National Park"
                style="max-width: 500px; height: auto; display: block; margin: 8px 0;" />

        <p><i>That</i> kind of arch.</p>

        <p>
            If you've been wondering why most of the pages in
            <a href="/Calculators/Directory">the Collection</a> are
            still missing, it's because I'm here in the Beehive state and not
            at my home (where most of my stuff and will to work is).
        </p>

        <p>But you know what I do have?</p>

        <img
                src="https://i.postimg.cc/sxnMzT9j/IMG_0199.jpg"
                alt="HP 50g in front of Turret Arch"
                style="max-width: 500px; height: auto; display: block; margin: 8px 0;" />

        <p>
            That's right. Most people out there can easily say that they have
            a calculator. Some of them can say that their calculators are
            cooler than all the other ones.
        </p>

        <p>
            But can they say that their calculator has been to Arches National
            Park?
        </p>

        <p>
            <sup>Yes, I did take it to Delicate Arch. No, I did not remember to
                take a picture of it <u>with</u> Delicate Arch.</sup>
        </p>

        <img
                src="https://i.postimg.cc/sDDWLh9Z/IMG_0209.jpg"
                alt="HP 50g in front of Balanced Rock"
                style="max-width: 500px; height: auto; display: block; margin: 8px 0;" />
        <img
                src="https://i.postimg.cc/hGxQmbgr/IMG_0204.jpg"
                alt="HP 50g lying under the North Window Arch"
                style="max-width: 500px; height: auto; display: block; margin: 8px 0;" />
    </div>
